    "created_at": "2023-09-12T08:59:17Z",
    "updated_at": "2023-09-12T08:59:17Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Hello,\r\nI have the impression that for all contracts deployed with a proxy, the \"2Step\" procedure implemented in the implementation contract (if present) loses its interested if the proxy admin does not implement this too for the following reason : \r\n\r\n- The proxy admin is more important that the storage of the proxy (e.g TransparentProxy) since you can upgrade the proxy to a new implementation contract.\r\nFor example, if you perform an error during the ownership/admin transmission on the proxy storage (e.g TransparentProxy), you can deploy a new implementation to fix it (not good, but possible)\r\n\r\n- If you make an error during the transmission of the proxy admin, game over.\r\n\r\nFor the gas cost analysis, not really the good person unfortunately.",
